archimate:BusinessObject.name: Interoperability Specification
archimate:BusinessObject.documentation:
DESCRIPTION: An Interoperability Specification is a document of the highest possible level of granularity on an EIRA SBB, formulated as an agreed normative statement in design terms on a legal, organisational, semantic, or technical attribute of an European Public Service. It can refer to existing standards or specifications
Source: ISA2 â€“ EIA Action
IoP dimensions: Structural IoP, Behavioral IoP, Governance IoP
